<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<graphml xmlns="http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns http://graphml.graphdrawing.org/xmlns/1.0/graphml.xsd">
  <key id="d11" for="edge" attr.name="type" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d10" for="edge" attr.name="seq" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d9" for="edge" attr.name="notes" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d8" for="edge" attr.name="flow_id" attr.type="long" />
  <key id="d7" for="node" attr.name="notes" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d6" for="node" attr.name="service" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d5" for="node" attr.name="name" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d4" for="graph" attr.name="graph_usable" attr.type="boolean" />
  <key id="d3" for="graph" attr.name="categories" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d2" for="graph" attr.name="notes" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d1" for="graph" attr.name="link" attr.type="string" />
  <key id="d0" for="graph" attr.name="name" attr.type="string" />
  <graph edgedefault="directed">
    <node id="UserConsumerWeb">
      <data key="d5">Web Browser User</data>
      <data key="d6">UserConsumerWeb</data>
      <data key="d7">WORKLOAD_PEEK: User logs in, creates account, defines S3 keys for the server, views metadata, defines workflows (retiming, deinterlacing, noise removal/retexturing, IMF wrapping), selects clips, and submits jobs. Recommended browser is Chrome.</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EC2_WebJobManager">
      <data key="d5">Web Server / Job Manager</data>
      <data key="d6">EC2</data>
      <data key="d7">WORKLOAD_PEEK: Runs Cinnafilm's Pixel strings web server and job manager on an EC2 instance. Handles user login, account creation, and S3 key management. The web server interacts with the database to display metadata. The Job Manager orchestrates metadata extraction (via Lambda), saves metadata to the DB, estimates job costs based on clip metadata, and submits jobs to the GPU cluster (up to 200 in parallel per region). It coordinates with an internal Asset Manager component for copying input/output clips to/from S3. Also directs the optional IMF wrapping process. It handles GPU instance failures by shutting down problematic instances and starting new ones. Current setup is a single instance, scaling to ~100 users, with future plans for real-time failover.</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DB_Metadata">
      <data key="d5">Metadata Database</data>
      <data key="d6">ThirdParty</data>
      <data key="d7">DATA_PEEK: Caches and stores metadata extracted from S3 video clips. The web server queries this database to display metadata to users, and the Job Manager saves metadata to it. Also used by the web server to calculate job costs based on clip length.</data>
    </node>
    <node id="S3_CustomerBuckets">
      <data key="d5">Customer S3 Buckets</data>
      <data key="d6">S3</data>
      <data key="d7">DATA_PEEK: Stores input video clips uploaded by users. Users manage their own buckets. Processed output video clips are written back to these buckets. GPU clusters are deployed in regions (US West, US East, and Ireland) close to customer buckets to minimize egress costs.</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Lambda_MediaInfo">
      <data key="d5">MediaInfo Lambda Function</data>
      <data key="d6">Lambda</data>
      <data key="d7">WORKLOAD_PEEK: Runs `MediaInfo` software to extract metadata from video clips stored in S3. Triggered by the Job Manager. These calls run in the background, allowing metadata to be filled in asynchronously in the user's browser.</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EC2_GPUCluster">
      <data key="d5">G3 GPU Processing Cluster</data>
      <data key="d6">EC2</data>
      <data key="d7">WORKLOAD_PEEK: A cluster of GPU-enabled EC2 instances (G3 family) for parallel video processing. Performs retiming (Warmhole), deinterlacing (Spacetime), and noise removal/retexturing (Dark Energy). Capable of running up to 200 jobs concurrently per region. Writes processed output to local disk before transfer to S3. Includes Asset Manager functionality for copying data to/from S3. Located in US West, US East, and Ireland.</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EC2_IMFWrapping">
      <data key="d5">IMF Wrapping Service</data>
      <data key="d6">EC2</data>
      <data key="d7">WORKLOAD_PEEK: A specialized processing service, likely running on EC2 instances. It performs interoperable master format (IMF) wrapping for processed video, which is often required for publishing to platforms like Netflix. Triggered by the Job Manager when IMF is selected in the user's workflow. Receives data from the GPU cluster, performs the wrapping, and then returns the result for final S3 transfer via the Asset Manager.</data>
    </node>
    <edge source="UserConsumerWeb" target="EC2_WebJobManager" id="0">
      <data key="d8">0</data>
      <data key="d9">User logs in and creates an account on the Pixel strings server via their web browser.</data>
      <data key="d10">0</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UserConsumerWeb" target="EC2_WebJobManager" id="1">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">User enters their S3 access keys into the web browser, which are sent to the Web Server / Job Manager for bucket access.</data>
      <data key="d10">1</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UserConsumerWeb" target="EC2_WebJobManager" id="2">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">User defines the desired workflow (e.g., Warmhole, Spacetime, Dark Energy, optional IMF), selects one or more clips, and submits the job.</data>
      <data key="d10">0</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UserConsumerWeb" target="EC2_WebJobManager" id="3">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">User confirms the job submission after reviewing the cost estimate.</data>
      <data key="d10">4</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="UserConsumerWeb" target="S3_CustomerBuckets" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">User uploads input video clips directly to their own S3 bucket.</data>
      <data key="d10">0</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="Lambda_MediaInfo" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">The Job Manager uses the Lambda function to initiate metadata extraction from S3 clips.</data>
      <data key="d10">2</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="DB_Metadata" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">The Job Manager saves the extracted metadata to the Metadata Database.</data>
      <data key="d10">6</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="DB_Metadata" id="1">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">The Web Server queries the Metadata Database to retrieve and display clip metadata to the user.</data>
      <data key="d10">7</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="DB_Metadata" id="2">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The Job Manager retrieves clip length/metadata from the Database to estimate job costs.</data>
      <data key="d10">1</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="UserConsumerWeb" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">The Web Server displays the clip metadata to the user in their browser.</data>
      <data key="d10">9</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="UserConsumerWeb" id="1">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The server provides a cost estimate for the job to the user.</data>
      <data key="d10">3</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="EC2_GPUCluster" id="0">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The Job Manager instructs the Asset Manager component (associated with the GPU cluster) to prepare for copying the input clip from S3 to local disk.</data>
      <data key="d10">5</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="EC2_GPUCluster" id="1">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The Job Manager sends job details, including the selected workflow and input clip paths, to the GPU cluster for processing.</data>
      <data key="d10">8</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="EC2_GPUCluster" id="2">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The Job Manager instructs the Asset Manager component (associated with the GPU cluster) to copy the final output clip (either directly processed or IMF wrapped) to S3.</data>
      <data key="d10">11</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_WebJobManager" target="EC2_IMFWrapping" id="0">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">If IMF format is selected in the workflow, the Job Manager orchestrates the IMF wrapping process after GPU processing is complete.</data>
      <data key="d10">8.1</data>
      <data key="d11">meta</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DB_Metadata" target="EC2_WebJobManager" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">The Database returns metadata to the Web Server.</data>
      <data key="d10">8</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DB_Metadata" target="EC2_WebJobManager" id="1">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The Database returns data required for cost estimation to the Job Manager.</data>
      <data key="d10">2</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="S3_CustomerBuckets" target="Lambda_MediaInfo" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">Metadata flows back from S3 to the Lambda function.</data>
      <data key="d10">4</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="S3_CustomerBuckets" target="EC2_GPUCluster" id="0">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">Input clip data is transferred from S3 to the G3 local disk.</data>
      <data key="d10">7</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="S3_CustomerBuckets" target="UserConsumerWeb" id="0">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">User accesses the final processed video file directly from their S3 bucket.</data>
      <data key="d10">13</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="Lambda_MediaInfo" target="S3_CustomerBuckets" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">The MediaInfo Lambda function retrieves metadata from video clips stored in the S3 bucket.</data>
      <data key="d10">3</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="Lambda_MediaInfo" target="EC2_WebJobManager" id="0">
      <data key="d8">1</data>
      <data key="d9">The Lambda function sends the extracted metadata back to the Job Manager.</data>
      <data key="d10">5</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_GPUCluster" target="S3_CustomerBuckets" id="0">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The Asset Manager (running on/with the GPU cluster) pulls the input clip data from the customer's S3 bucket to the local disk of the G3 instances.</data>
      <data key="d10">6</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_GPUCluster" target="S3_CustomerBuckets" id="1">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">The Asset Manager (running on/with the GPU cluster) pushes the processed output clip from local disk to the customer's S3 bucket.</data>
      <data key="d10">12</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_GPUCluster" target="EC2_IMFWrapping" id="0">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">Processed video data is sent from the GPU cluster to the IMF Wrapping Service if IMF format is selected.</data>
      <data key="d10">9</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="EC2_IMFWrapping" target="EC2_GPUCluster" id="0">
      <data key="d8">2</data>
      <data key="d9">IMF wrapped data is returned from the IMF Wrapping Service to the Asset Manager component within the GPU cluster for S3 upload.</data>
      <data key="d10">10</data>
      <data key="d11">data</data>
    </edge>
    <data key="d0">Pixel strings video processing platform</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BZ32w0SSAoY</data>
    <data key="d2">Cinnafilm's Pixel strings platform processes video for retiming, deinterlacing, upscaling, noise removal, and retexturing. Users upload video clips to their own S3 buckets, define workflows via a web browser, and submit jobs for GPU-accelerated processing. The platform offers services like Warmhole (retiming), Spacetime (deinterlacing), and Dark Energy (noise removal/retexturing). It supports up to 200 parallel jobs per region across US West, US East, and Ireland, leveraging G3 instances. Metadata extraction happens in the background using Lambda. An optional IMF (Interoperable Master Format) wrapping step is available for Netflix publishing. The web server currently runs as a single EC2 instance but is designed for scalability and future failover. GPU failures are handled by the job manager to ensure high availability.</data>
    <data key="d3">compute_intensive, data_ingestion, interactive</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
